About this Addendum
This China Addendum (“Addendum”) is a local supplement of the Careers Privacy Policy of Macquarie Group (“Careers Privacy Policy”) and intends to highlight the specific principles and rules that Macquarie (which includes Macquarie Investment Advisory (Beijing) Co. Ltd., Macquarie Investment Advisory (Beijing) Co. Ltd., Shanghai Branch, Macquarie Investment Consulting (Shanghai) Co. Ltd., Macquarie Commodities Trading (Shanghai) Co. Ltd., Macquarie Securities (Australia) Limited Shanghai Representative Office, and their branches, subsidiaries and related entities) (the “Company” or “we”) follows when processing your personal information during the recruitment process in accordance with the applicable laws of the People’s Republic of China (“China”, and for the purpose of this Addendum only, “China” refers to the mainland of the People’s Republic of China, excluding Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, Macau Administrative Region and Taiwan region).
Before you submit your resume and/or job application form to us, please read this Addendum carefully and understand the information provided herein. Please indicate your consent and separate consent to the specific processing activities described herein by checking the appropriate box and signing at the end of this Addendum.
Sensitive personal information
"Sensitive personal information" is subject to special protection under Chinese law. Sensitive personal information means the personal information that, once disclosed or illegally used, is easy to infringe upon the personal dignity of natural persons or endanger the safety of human life and property, including such information as biometric identification, religious belief, specific identity, medical treatment and health, financial accounts, and whereabouts, as well as personal information of minors under the age of 14.
We need to process your sensitive personal information (including your identification document information, criminal records and information on civil proceedings to consider your job application and decide whether to enter into an employment contract with you. Without such information, we may not be able to proceed with your application.
We will not process your sensitive personal information unless we have obtained your separate consent or are otherwise required by applicable laws and regulations. We take strict measures to protect your sensitive personal information.
Transferring your personal information outside of China
As Macquarie adopts a unified global human resources management framework, in order to consider and process your application, we need to provide your personal information to recipients located outside of China, including certain overseas affiliates of Macquarie group located outside of China.
In order to transfer your personal information to the overseas recipients, we will obtain your separate consent, and will ensure that the overseas recipients' processing of personal information meets the personal information protection standards prescribed by the applicable laws and regulations.
Names and contact details of the overseas recipients, the purposes and manners of processing, and the types of personal information to be transferred are set out in the below table.
