Your rights
You are entitled to a series of legal rights with respect to your personal information held by us, including the rights to:
be informed of the processing of your personal information;
withdraw your consent to process your personal information at any time. Your withdrawal of your consent will not affect the validity of the personal information processing activities we have conducted based on your consent prior to withdrawal. However, please note that even if you withdraw your consent, we may still have the right to process your personal information based on another legal basis;
access your personal information and obtain a copy of it;
If you request the transfer of your personal information to a designated personal information processor, we will provide a means of transfer subject to the conditions prescribed by the applicable laws and regulations;
request correction and/or supplement of inaccurate or incomplete personal information;
request us to delete your personal information under certain circumstances. However, please note that we still have the right to retain your personal information even if you request us to delete it prior to the expiry of the retention period prescribed by the applicable laws and regulations;
stop or restrict our processing of your personal information under certain circumstances. However, please note that we are legally entitled to refuse your request under certain circumstances;
request an explanation of our personal information processing rules;
request explanation and refuse to be subject to a decision based solely on automated processing when we make a decision by an automated decision-making mode that has a material impact on your rights and interests; and
complain to and report illegal personal information processing activities to the applicable personal information protection authority.
You may exercise your rights by emailing us at
privacy@macquarie.com
.
